@Nicknakin 
For me, I'm able to play online. I just have to launch the game tens of times before it works. I have a script launching Elden Ring on a loop until the active window is named "ELDEN RING™".

The game doesn't crash, it simply gets stuck, which makes me think the process gets blocked and vulkan context gets lost because of some desync. Not much to report.

@imaginaryPineapple
I see. The behavior on my machine is either a non-launch or a white-screen followed by a crash. I never get past the white screen after the EAC launcher pops up. If anyone capable of diagnosing the issue needs more information feel free to @ me, more than happy contribute to figuring out what's going on.

Here's the latest log from an attempt to run. https://gist.github.com/Nicknakin/b8536c87abeb2a0353298ec2909efb9a

My issue seems to be solved by setting `PROTON_NO_D3D11=1` in the launch options.
The Flatpak version of steam did no difference on my part.
